Samantha Rawcliffe, 40, lost control of her car and crashed her car last May .
The mother-of-two lost control and was shaken uncontrollably .
In the days after the accident she was unable to walk or talk .
She was taken to Royal Preston Hospital to have a cocktail of drugs .
But she was diagnosed with a rare neurological disorder called functional neurological disorder - an umbrella term for a variety of neurological symptoms that doctors cannot explain .